    <fr:title text="Judgement Calculi">Judgement Calculi</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>3</fr:month>
      <fr:day>31</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors />
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>Given a set of primitive relation symbols <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {R}]]></fr:tex>, the judgements are defined as follows.
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[     \mathcal {J} := R(\overline {e}) \,\, | \,\, \{x\} \, \, \mathcal {J} \,\, | \,\, \mathcal {J} \vdash  \mathcal {J}   ]]></fr:tex>
  The proof rules are then "obvious":
  <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[R(\overline {e})]]></fr:tex>: Supplied by the background theory</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x\} \, \, \mathcal {J}]]></fr:tex>: Generalization and specialization</fr:li>
    <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {J} \vdash  \mathcal {J}]]></fr:tex>: Abstraction and application</fr:li></fr:ul></fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
